---
import { PERSON } from '../consts';
---

<section class="hero">
	<div class="hero-content">
		<p class="hero-greeting">Hi, I'm</p>
		<h1>{PERSON.name}</h1>
		<p class="hero-title">
			<span class="accent">{PERSON.title}</span> · {PERSON.experience} · {PERSON.location}
		</p>
		<p class="hero-availability">{PERSON.availability}</p>

		<div class="hero-description">
			<p>
				Full stack software engineer with 7+ years building enterprise applications on AWS and Red
				Hat OpenShift - mostly Java and Spring Boot on the backend, Angular or React on the frontend.
				A lot of my work has involved event-driven systems with Apache Kafka.
			</p>
			<p>
				Over the last couple of years I've gone deep into applied AI - RAG pipelines, tool-calling
				agents, and LLM integration with Spring AI, Pinecone, and pgvector. For my master's capstone
				at Kennesaw State, I built a production-grade conversational AI with an LLM-as-Judge layer to
				cut down on hallucinations - a full Spring Boot + React app, containerized and deployed on
				AWS.
			</p>
		</div>
	</div>
</section>

<style>
	.hero {
		padding: 2.5rem 0 3rem;
	}

	.hero-greeting {
		font-size: 1.1rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray));
		margin-bottom: 0.25rem;
	}

	.hero h1 {
		font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 3.5rem);
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		letter-spacing: -0.02em;
	}

	.hero-title {
		font-size: 1.2rem;
		margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
	}

	.hero-availability {
		font-size: 0.95rem;
		font-weight: 700;
		color: var(--accent);
		margin-bottom: 1.75rem;
	}

	.accent {
		color: var(--accent);
		font-weight: 700;
	}

	.hero-description {
		display: grid;
		grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
		gap: 1.5rem 2.5rem;
		max-width: 100%;
	}

	.hero-description p {
		margin: 0;
		font-size: 1.05rem;
		color: rgb(var(--gray-dark));
		line-height: 1.8;
	}

	@media (max-width: 720px) {
		.hero-description {
			grid-template-columns: 1fr;
			gap: 1.25rem;
		}
	}
</style>
